Makes full template power available to blog posts.Previously, I got weired errors when using e.g. `{% url path %}`nin blog posts:nn```n*** Error while buildingn'__CACTUS_SITE__'nTraceback (most recent call last):n...nFile /usr/local/lib/python2.7/dist-packages/Cactus-3.3.2-py2.7.egg/cactus/template_tags.py, line 52, in urlnsite = context['__CACTUS_SITE__']n  File /usr/local/lib/python2.7/dist-packages/Django-1.6.11-py2.7.egg/django/template/context.py, line 56, in __getitem__nraise KeyError(key)nKeyError: '__CACTUS_SITE__'n```nnIt turns out that `getNode` needs the full site contextnto work probably.nTherefore this commit creates the site context and adds it to all postContexts.nNow I can use `{% url path %}` and the likes in my blog posts.n
